          "description": "Transfer toasted chiles to a bowl and cover with hot water. Weight them down with a small plate so they stay submerged. Soak until soft and the edges no longer crack when bent, about 15 minutes. Drain, reserving a few tablespoons of soaking liquid in case you need to thin the paste.",
